 UK today. Through its analysis, the book demonstrates how polygamy and polygamous wives are subjected to imperialist and orientalist discourses which dehumanise them for practising a relationship that has existed for millennia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminist jurisprudencezEngland. 0aFeminist jurisprudencezWales. 0aPolygamyxLaw and legislationzEngland. 0aPolygamyxLaw and legislationzWales. 7aLAW / Family Law / Marriage.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152920969340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529210804?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529210804423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529210804/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles